Product Roadmap – Feature X

## 1. Overview
Feature X is designed to improve user onboarding through guided tutorials, interactive tooltips, and smarter default settings.

Goal:
- Reduce drop-offs in the first 7 days
- Improve early user engagement

---

## 2. Goals & KPIs
- Reduce onboarding drop-off rate by 20%
- Increase activation rate from 45% to 60%
- Achieve 12 min average session time (first week)
- Collect 500+ user feedback responses

---

## 3. Feature Scope
- Interactive guided tutorials for key workflows
- Contextual tooltips for major actions
- Smart default settings based on user type
- Analytics tracking for onboarding completion

---

## 4. Timeline & Milestones
- Design mockups → April 10
- Internal QA → April 20
- Beta launch → Late April
- Iteration → Ongoing based on feedback

---

## 5. Dependencies
- UI/UX team for design mockups
- Backend APIs for onboarding events
- Analytics integration

---

## 6. Risks & Challenges
- Delays in design approvals  
- Technical bugs during beta  
- Low engagement if tutorials feel intrusive  

---

## 7. Next Steps
- Finalize designs  
- Conduct QA testing  
- Launch beta  
- Iterate based on user feedback  
